 between $\\rho_X$ and $\\rho_Z$\nand we show that the total dark energy density\n$\\rho_{DE}(t)=\\rho_X(t)+\\rho_Z(t)$ always remains a finite fraction of the\ncritical density at any time, providing a specific model of early dark energy.\nWe discuss the implication of this result for the coincidence problem and we\nestimate the model parameters by means of a full likelihood analysis using\ncurrent CMB, SNe Ia and BAO data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Apr 2011 16:35:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Jun 2011 21:22:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 21 Jun 2011 11:04:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-06-22"}
